The United States strongly condemns the terrorist attack in Grand-Bassam, Côte d'Ivoire. They offer their condolences to the families of the victims and praise the bravery of the security personnel who responded to the situation. The Department of State is coordinating with partners to ensure the safety of American citizens in the country. The United States stands with the people of Côte d'Ivoire and will support the government in its efforts to strengthen governance and economic institutions. They are also committed to fighting terrorism in partnership with regional governments and international partners.